cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.NA.

Reasoning: 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper deals with geometric objects (disks) and their coverings and piercings. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper presents exact and approximation algorithms for the two-center problems. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper deals with combinatorial problems involving sets of disks. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is less likely but still possible as the paper involves finding optimal solutions for covering and piercing disks, which can be viewed as a game between the algorithm and the input. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is less likely but still possible as the paper may involve numerical methods for solving the two-center problems.
